This week, my main focus was configuring and preparing our platform integrations for formal review. For many of the external services Lucidity connects with, our integration relies on a custom developer application that acts as our information hub and dashboard. Setting these up required mapping out our scope permissions. I spent time auditing our codebase to know the exact API endpoints equivalents we use to make sure we request access to exactly what we need, no more and no less. By the end of the week, all of the requests had been sent out, and our dashboards were set up to start using our pending API access in Lucidity as soon as they're approved.
